Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
fixBondPad(25.10)                                            fixBondPad(25.10)

Name
       fixBondPad - Assigns a fixed status to a specified bond pad

Syntax
       fixBondPad

       [-help]

       {{-ioInstName <InstName>[-pinName <pinName>]}

        | -selected}

       Assigns  a  fixed  status to a specified bond pad. This restricts other
       bond pad commands from modifying the bond pad.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each fixBondPad parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man fixBondPad

       -ioInstName <instName>
              Specifies  the  name  of the I/O instance whose bond pad will be
              assigned as fixed.

       -pinName <pinName>
              Specifies the name of the pin inside the instance.

       -selected
              Assigns a fixed status to a selected bond pad.

              You must first select the bond pad in the design  display  area,
              then use this parameter to assign the fixed status.

Example
              * The  following  command assigns a fixed status to the bond pad
                in I/O instance pad_addr[30]:

                fixBondPad -ioInstName {pad_addr[30]}

